🔺 Problem 610 – Triangle Judgement

Today’s problem was a simple yet logical SQL question based on basic mathematics.

🧠 Problem Summary

We are given three columns:

x

y

z

Each row represents three sides of a triangle.

We need to determine whether these sides can form a valid triangle.

📐 Key Concept – Triangle Inequality Rule

A triangle is valid if:

x + y > z

x + z > y

y + z > x

If all conditions are true → "Yes"
Otherwise → "No"

🧑‍💻 SQL Solution
SELECT 
    x,
    y,
    z,
    CASE 
        WHEN x + y > z 
         AND x + z > y 
         AND y + z > x 
        THEN 'Yes'
        ELSE 'No'
    END AS triangle
FROM Triangle;
